### generateReproducer() {#a7ea4fb4d6b0198f2b6eac325a8d93031}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static void generateReproducer (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/cmpinst">CmpInst</a> &#42; Cond, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/module">Module</a> &#42; M, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef</a>&lt; ReproducerEntry &gt; Stack, ConstraintInfo &amp; Info, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dominatortree">DominatorTree</a> &amp; DT)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Helper function to generate a reproducer function for simplifying <code>Cond</code>.

The reproducer function contains a series of @llvm.assume calls, one for each condition in <code>Stack</code>. For each condition, the operand instruction are cloned until we reach operands that have an entry in <code>Value2Index</code>. Those will then be added as function arguments. <code>DT</code> is used to order cloned instructions. The reproducer function will get added to <code>M</code>, if it is non-null. Otherwise no reproducer function is generated.
